# Web Research

## Goal
Find new high-quality sources to fill knowledge gaps in the {{config.project.name}} wiki.

<workflow>

{{#if (eq config.workflows.ingestion_style "autonomous")}}
<step n="0" goal="Assess wiki maturity before autonomous research">
  <action>Count the number of source summary pages in `wiki/sources/`</action>
  <action>Count the number of entity and concept pages in `wiki/entities/` and `wiki/concepts/`</action>
  <check if="wiki has fewer than {{config.maturity.research_sources_min}} ingested sources">
    <critical>The wiki is too sparse for autonomous research. With fewer than {{config.maturity.research_sources_min}} sources, there is not enough context to identify meaningful knowledge gaps — searching now would be unfocused and produce low-quality results.</critical>
    <action>FALL BACK to human-guided mode for this operation: ask the user what topics, questions, or areas they want you to research. Use their direction instead of gap analysis.</action>
    <action>Present: "Your wiki has [N] sources — not enough for me to autonomously identify gaps. What would you like me to search for? Give me a topic, question, or area of {{config.project.domain}} to focus on."</action>
    <action>WAIT for user input. Use their response as the research focus for the remaining steps.</action>
    <action>After this research session completes, do NOT auto-chain the full autonomous cycle. Present recommendations to the user as in deliberate mode — the wiki needs more human-curated foundation before autonomous cycles are productive.</action>
  </check>
  <check if="wiki has {{config.maturity.research_sources_min}}+ sources but no entity or concept pages (sources ingested but not compiled)">
    <action>Warn: "Your wiki has sources but they haven't been compiled into entity/concept pages yet. Research will be more effective after running update-entities and update-concepts. Proceeding with gap analysis based on source summaries only."</action>
  </check>
</step>
{{/if}}

<step n="1" goal="Identify knowledge gaps">
  <action>Review `wiki/index.md` and `wiki/overview.md` to understand current coverage</action>
  <action>If the user specified a topic, focus gap analysis on that area</action>
  <action>Check `wiki/log.md` for recent lint reports that identified gaps</action>
  <action>List the top 3-5 gaps worth filling</action>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Formulate search queries">
  <action>For each identified gap, craft 2-3 targeted search queries</action>
  <action>Include domain-specific terminology relevant to {{config.project.domain}}</action>
  <action>Prefer queries that target authoritative sources for this wiki's domain — primary documents, first-hand accounts, and recognized expertise. Avoid summaries-of-summaries unless they cite well.</action>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Execute search">
  <action>Search the web using the crafted queries</action>
  <action>Collect candidate sources: title, URL, publication date, author/publisher, brief description</action>
  <action>Aim for 5-10 candidates per gap area</action>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Evaluate and rank candidates">
  <action>For each candidate, assess provenance using the universal taxonomy — primary vs. secondary, first-hand vs. derived, authoritative vs. anecdotal, recent vs. dated — alongside relevance to the wiki's domain and depth of coverage</action>
  <action>Cross-reference against `wiki/sources/` to exclude already-ingested material</action>
  <action>Rank by quality score (credibility × relevance × recency)</action>
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Present recommendations">
  <action>Present the top 3-5 sources per gap area with: title, URL, date, provenance assessment (the taxonomy markers above), and a relevance explanation</action>
  <action>Group recommendations by gap area</action>
  <action>Note which existing wiki pages would benefit from each source</action>
</step>

<step n="6" goal="Queue for ingestion">
{{#if (eq config.workflows.ingestion_style "autonomous")}}
  <action>Auto-select recommended sources that are at minimum: primary OR authoritative, AND relevance >= high. Reject sources that are only secondary/derived OR anecdotal unless they are the only available coverage of a real gap. Log the selection criteria and which sources passed/failed for post-hoc audit with `[AUTO]` prefix.</action>
  <action>For each selected source, fetch the content into `raw/` using the appropriate conversion method (URL fetch and convert to markdown, download PDF, etc.)</action>
  <action>Log the research session in `wiki/log.md` including: gaps targeted, queries used, sources found, sources selected, sources rejected with reasons</action>
  <action>Proceed directly to batch ingestion of the fetched sources — invoke the `wforge-batch-ingest` workflow with the new source list</action>
  <action>After batch ingestion completes, invoke `wforge-cross-reference` to verify link integrity across all new and updated pages</action>
  <action>Then invoke `wforge-reindex` to rebuild the wiki index</action>
  <action>Finally, run a lightweight lint pass via `wforge-lint-wiki` to identify any issues introduced during this cycle</action>
  <critical>This is ONE autonomous cycle: research → fetch → ingest → cross-reference → reindex → lint → report. Do NOT loop back to gap identification. After the lint report, STOP and present a consolidated cycle summary to the user.</critical>
{{else}}
  <action>Ask the user which recommended sources to ingest</action>
  <action>For approved sources, either queue them for batch ingestion or begin single-source ingestion</action>
  <action>Log the research session in `wiki/log.md`</action>
{{/if}}
</step>

</workflow>
